## Skills

Domain knowledge lives in `.claude/skills/` as `SKILL.md` files — one per domain. Each has a CSO-style frontmatter `description:` that names *when* to use it (specific tables, file paths, function names, task verbs).

**1% rule — read aggressively.** Before responding to any non-trivial task, if there is even a 1% chance a skill in `.claude/skills/` applies, Read it first. Err on the side of reading too many rather than too few. It is always cheaper to read a skill you did not need than to work without context and guess wrong.

